(1. Introduction) Tj T*
(1.1 Purpose) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(This document defines the functional and non-functional requirements for the Smart Irrigation) Tj T*
(Management System. The system will enable farmers and farm administrators to remotely monitor) Tj T*
(farms, automate irrigation, manage crops, and generate reports using IoT sensor data.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1.2 Project Scope) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The Smart Irrigation Management System aims to:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Monitor live sensor readings.) Tj T*
(Automate irrigation based on soil moisture.) Tj T*
(Reduce water consumption.) Tj T*
(Improve crop yield.) Tj T*
(Provide reports and analytics.) Tj T*
(Enable remote farm management.) Tj T*
(1.3 Intended Users) Tj T*
(Farm Owners) Tj T*
(Supervisors) Tj T*
(Caretakers) Tj T*
(System Administrators) Tj T*
(2. Business Objective) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The client currently operates irrigation manually, leading to:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Excessive water usage) Tj T*
(Delayed irrigation) Tj T*
(Crop damage) Tj T*
(High operational cost) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The proposed solution should:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Automate irrigation.) Tj T*
(Reduce manual intervention.) Tj T*
(Provide real-time farm monitoring.) Tj T*
(Improve productivity.) Tj T*
(Reduce water wastage.) Tj T*
(3. Functional Requirements) Tj T*
(Module 1 - Authentication) Tj T*
ET
